      "patient_reported_reason": "Paediatric diabetes review — HbA1c and pump settings",
      "clinician_notes": "Subjective: 16-year-old male with T1DM since age 10, currently on basal-bolus insulin regimen. Parents present. No recent hypoglycaemic episodes requiring assistance. Blood glucose readings mostly 5-9 mmol/L pre-meal. Occasional post-prandial spikes to 13-14 mmol/L. Active — plays football 5x/week. Good understanding of carbohydrate counting.\n\nObjective: Weight 52 kg, Height 158 cm, BMI 20.8. HbA1c 52 mmol/mol (6.9%) — at target. No injection site lipohypertrophy. BP 108/68 mmHg.\n\nAssessment: Well-controlled T1DM on basal-bolus regimen. HbA1c at target for age. Post-prandial excursions consistent with underestimated carbohydrate portions at some meals.\n\nPlan: Continue Lantus 14 units at bedtime. Continue NovoRapid with meals on carb ratio 1:10. Dietician review to refine carb counting for complex meals. Review in 3 months. Annual microalbuminuria and eye screening due.",
